.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH ox-query 1  "ox-query " 
.SH NAME
ox\-query \- Query the dependency graph (Bazel\-style)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBox\-query\fR [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-f\fR|\fB\-\-file\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIEXPRESSION\fR> 
.SH DESCRIPTION
Query the dependency graph (Bazel\-style)
.PP
Supports: deps(X), rdeps(X), allpaths(X, Y)
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Output JSON instead of human\-readable text
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-file\fR \fI<FILE>\fR [default: Oxymakefile.toml]
Oxymakefile path
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
<\fIEXPRESSION\fR>
Query expression, e.g. \*(Aqdeps(annotate)\*(Aq, \*(Aqrdeps(data)\*(Aq, \*(Aqallpaths(data, annotate)\*(Aq
